info.name: Genomic Order Management - ALPHA - API Collection - INT Environment
info.description:
This is the postman collection for the following

1\. Test directory API -

2\. Routing API

3\. Order Management API - INT Enviroment

Configuration Steps

a) Import the collection into postman

b) At the collection level in Authorisation add your application apikey value. To get apikey follow steps in [https://digital.nhs.uk/developer/getting-started](https://digital.nhs.uk/developer/getting-started) by creating an account and registering an application for integration.

item.description:
This collection test the following scenario

1. Send a test request for Rare Disease R132.1 using requestor org "699W0" to /FHIR/R4 endpoint using transaction message. Capture the logical Id for Patient and Service Request. There is no specimen in the initial request
    
2. A generic /ServiceRequest GET using "699W0" as requester.
    
3. A ServiceRequest/LOGICAL_ID GET can confirming is the ID's match
    
4. Attach a specimen to the test request
    
5. Get the specimen and check Id
    
6. Update the specimen
    
7. Get the specimen and check Id
    
8. Attach a report to the specimen
    
9. Get report and check Id of the report
    
10. Update the final report
    
11. Get report and check Id of the report
